Some governorship aspirants of the All Progressives Congress (APC) who lost out to Governor Oluwarotimi Akeredolu at the party’s primaries have been drafted into the state campaign council. State Chairman of the APC, Engr. Ade Adetimehin was named Director General of Campaign Committee while Governor Akeredolu is Chairman of the Campaign Council. Former governorship aspirants named in the campaign council were Chief Olus9la Oke, Ife Oyedele, D. I. Kekemeke, Segun Abraham, Jimi Odimayo, and Ambassador Sola Iji. Other members of the campaign council were Senator Borrofice, Bunmi Tunji-Ojo – Ade Adeogun, Timehin Adelegbe, Mayowa Akinfolarin, Senator Yele Omogunwa, Dayo Faduyile, Pius Osunyikanmi, Kole Oluwajana, Bamidele Oloyelogun. Ondo Commissioner for Information and Orientation, Donald Ojogo, was appointed Chairman of the Media and Publicity Committee while a spokesman for the APC, Alex Kalejaiye would serve as Secretary. Mr. Charles Fagbohunka is the chairman voting units canvassers Committee; Senator Tayo Alasoadura was named Chairman Finance and Resources Allocation while Alex Ajipe is chairman Civil Society and Support Groups committee.